{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BxEzDbPhfnNy3KY3KU2LEA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-2: Implement RalphDriver\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want Ralph wrapped in an `AgentDriver` implementation,\n     9→So that ralph-specific behavior is isolated in one file.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` exists, when inspected, then it implements `AgentDriver` with: `spawn()` (builds ralph.sh args), `parseOutput()` (parses ralph stderr + stream-json) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `run-helpers.ts` ralph-specific functions (`parseRalphMessage`, `parseIterationMessage`, `buildSpawnArgs`), when migration completes, then they're moved into `ralph.ts` and `run-helpers.ts` is deleted <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction).** Ralph becomes one implementation of `AgentDriver`.\n    19→\n    20→`RalphDriver` wraps `ralph.sh` invocation:\n    21→\n    22→```typescript\n    23→class RalphDriver implements AgentDriver {\n    24→  readonly name = 'ralph';\n    25→\n    26→  spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess {\n    27→    // Build ralph.sh args from SpawnOpts\n    28→    // Resolve ralph.sh path (from resolveRalphPath())\n    29→    // Spawn child process with correct env\n    30→    return childProcess;\n    31→  }\n    32→\n    33→  parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null {\n    34→    // Parse ralph stderr messages (iteration counts, story status)\n    35→    // Parse stream-json output from Claude CLI\n    36→    // Convert to AgentEvent discriminated union\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  getStatusFile(): string {\n    40→    return 'ralph/status.json';\n    41→  }\n    42→}\n    43→```\n    44→\n    45→Functions to migrate from `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` into `ralph.ts`:\n    46→- `parseRalphMessage()` — Parses ralph.sh stderr output for iteration counts, story completion\n    47→- `parseIterationMessage()` — Extracts iteration number from ralph output\n    48→- `buildSpawnArgs()` — Constructs the args array for spawning ralph.sh\n    49→- `resolveRalphPath()` — Finds ralph.sh in npm global or plugin directory\n    50→\n    51→Also migrate from `src/lib/stream-parser.ts`:\n    52→- Stream JSON parsing logic used to interpret Claude CLI output. Move to `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` (same file, new location under agents/).\n    53→\n    54→Migrate from `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts`:\n    55→- Ralph prompt generation. Move into `ralph.ts` or keep as a separate `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` if >100 lines.\n    56→\n    57→After migration, `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` should be deleted. All its exports are now in `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts`.\n    58→\n    59→## Files to Change\n    60→\n    61→- `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` — Create. Implement `RalphDriver` with `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`. Absorb functions from run-helpers.ts\n    62→- `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` — Move from `src/lib/stream-parser.ts`. Parse Claude CLI stream-json output\n    63→- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — Update. Re-export `RalphDriver` and stream parser\n    64→- `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` — Delete after migrating all functions to ralph.ts\n    65→- `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` — Delete after moving to agents/stream-parser.ts\n    66→- `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` — Move ralph prompt generation into agents/ directory\n    67→- All files importing from `run-helpers.ts` or `stream-parser.ts` — Update import paths\n    68→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CTXXCcQ8YHDUe6iJSvW3kn","session_id":"3ce6f3e2-c583-4074-ab3d-bf1fc6d87b66","uuid":"f8715307-0ecb-43cc-99b8-3d03b2b93a89","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:48:10.935Z"}
