{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014VmsrLbzaL8JyR9Msr2qPn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-1: Create AgentDriver Interface and Types\n     2→\n     3→## Status: done\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     8→\n     9→## Story\n    10→\n    11→As a developer,\n    12→I want an `AgentDriver` interface that abstracts agent execution,\n    13→So that Ralph can be replaced or supplemented without touching 28 files.\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→1. Given `src/lib/agents/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it exports `AgentDriver`, `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→2. Given the `AgentDriver` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `readonly name: string`, `spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess`, `parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null`, `getStatusFile(): string` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→3. Given the `SpawnOpts` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `storyKey: string`, `prompt: string`, `workDir: string`, `timeout: number`, `env?: Record<string, string>` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→4. Given the `AgentProcess` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `stdout: Readable`, `stderr: Readable`, `on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void`, `kill(signal?: string): void` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→5. Given the `AgentEvent` type, when inspected, then it is a discriminated union on `type` covering: `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `story-complete`, `story-failed`, `iteration`, `retry`, `result` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→6. Given `src/lib/agents/index.ts` exists, when inspected, then it re-exports all types from `./types.js` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→7. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→8. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→9. Given no file in `src/lib/agents/`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→10. Given `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` exists, when inspected, then it verifies the type exports are importable and the `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers all 8 event types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→\n    28→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    29→\n    30→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5): Create `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n    31→  - [x] Define and export `SpawnOpts` interface with `storyKey`, `prompt`, `workDir`, `timeout`, `env?`\n    32→  - [x] Import `Readable` from `node:stream`\n    33→  - [x] Define and export `AgentProcess` interface with `stdout`, `stderr`, `on('close')`, `kill()`\n    34→  - [x] Define and export `AgentEvent` discriminated union type with all 8 event types\n    35→  - [x] Define and export `AgentDriver` interface with `name`, `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`\n    36→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 6): Create `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n    37→  - [x] Re-export all types from `./types.js`\n    38→  - [x] Add placeholder comment for future driver registry and implementations\n    39→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 10): Create `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts`\n    40→  - [x] Verify all type exports are importable from the module\n    41→  - [x] Verify `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers all 8 event types via type-level tests\n    42→  - [x] Verify `AgentDriver` interface shape matches specification\n    43→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 7): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    44→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 8): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    45→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 9): Verify all new files are under 300 lines\n    46→\n    47→## Dev Notes\n    48→\n    49→### Architecture Compliance\n    50→\n    51→- **Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction):** This story creates the foundational types from architecture-v3.md Decision 3. The `AgentDriver` interface is the contract that `RalphDriver` (story 13-2) and future drivers must implement.\n    52→- **Decision 4 (Domain Subdirectories):** Files go under `src/lib/agents/` per the architecture's target file tree.\n    53→- **300-line limit (Decision 7, NFR5):** All new files must stay under 300 lines. This is a types-only story so files will be well under the limit.\n    54→\n    55→### Implementation Guidance\n    56→\n    57→This is a **types-only story**. No implementation code beyond interface definitions and the `index.ts` re-export facade.\n    58→\n    59→The `AgentProcess` interface wraps Node.js `ChildProcess` but abstracts it so future drivers (direct API calls, WebSocket connections) can implement it differently. Import `Readable` from `node:stream` for the stream types.\n    60→\n    61→`AgentEvent` is a discriminated union on `type`. The `parseOutput()` method converts raw agent output lines into typed events. Each driver knows its own output format.\n    62→\n    63→All types should be `export`ed (not `export default`) so they can be individually imported.\n    64→\n    65→### Type Design Notes\n    66→\n    67→```typescript\n    68→// src/lib/agents/types.ts\n    69→import type { Readable } from 'node:stream';\n    70→\n    71→export interface SpawnOpts {\n    72→  storyKey: string;\n    73→  prompt: string;\n    74→  workDir: string;\n    75→  timeout: number;\n    76→  env?: Record<string, string>;\n    77→}\n    78→\n    79→export interface AgentProcess {\n    80→  stdout: Readable;\n    81→  stderr: Readable;\n    82→  on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void;\n    83→  kill(signal?: string): void;\n    84→}\n    85→\n    86→export type AgentEvent =\n    87→  | { type: 'tool-start'; name: string }\n    88→  | { type: 'tool-complete'; name: string; args: string }\n    89→  | { type: 'text'; text: string }\n    90→  | { type: 'story-complete'; key: string; details: string }\n    91→  | { type: 'story-failed'; key: string; reason: string }\n    92→  | { type: 'iteration'; count: number }\n    93→  | { type: 'retry'; attempt: number; delay: number }\n    94→  | { type: 'result'; cost: number; sessionId: string };\n    95→\n    96→export interface AgentDriver {\n    97→  readonly name: string;\n    98→  spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess;\n    99→  parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null;\n   100→  getStatusFile(): string;\n   101→}\n   102→```\n   103→\n   104→### Testing Guidance\n   105→\n   106→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   107→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'`\n   108→- For a types-only story, tests verify that types are importable and that the discriminated union shape is correct. Use type-level assertions and runtime checks on type guard functions if applicable.\n   109→- Import convention: use `.js` extension for ESM resolution (e.g., `from '../types.js'`).\n   110→\n   111→### Previous Story Intelligence (12-4)\n   112→\n   113→- Story 12-4 completed successfully. All 3539 tests passing.\n   114→- Import boundaries test (`src/modules/__tests__/import-boundaries.test.ts`) enforces module isolation.\n   115→- Shared test utilities available at `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`.\n   116→\n   117→### Project Structure After This Story\n   118→\n   119→```\n   120→src/lib/agents/\n   121→├── types.ts          # AgentDriver, SpawnOpts, AgentProcess, AgentEvent\n   122→├── index.ts          # Re-export facade\n   123→└── __tests__/\n   124→    └── types.test.ts # Type import verification tests\n   125→```\n   126→\n   127→### References\n   128→\n   129→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md lines 173-213] — Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction) full specification\n   130→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 255-273] — Story 13-1 epic definition\n   131→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md] — Previous story learnings\n   132→\n   133→## Dev Agent Record\n   134→\n   135→### Implementation Plan\n   136→\n   137→Types-only story. Created three files under `src/lib/agents/`:\n   138→1. `types.ts` — All four type/interface exports matching the architecture spec exactly\n   139→2. `index.ts` — Barrel re-export with placeholder comment for future driver registry\n   140→3. `__tests__/types.test.ts` — 19 tests verifying importability, discriminated union coverage, and interface shape\n   141→\n   142→### Debug Log\n   143→\n   144→- Initial test had off-by-one in a mock `parseOutput` slice (`slice(5)` vs `slice(6)` for `\"TEXT: \"` prefix). Fixed immediately.\n   145→\n   146→### Completion Notes\n   147→\n   148→- All 10 acceptance criteria satisfied\n   149→- TypeScript build succeeds with zero errors\n   150→- Full test suite: 135 files, 3561 tests, all passing (22 new tests added, 0 regressions)\n   151→- File line counts: types.ts=56, index.ts=15, types.test.ts=238 — all well under 300-line limit\n   152→- Updated `src/lib/AGENTS.md` with new agents subsystem documentation\n   153→\n   154→## File List\n   155→\n   156→- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — Created. AgentDriver, SpawnOpts, AgentProcess, AgentEvent type definitions\n   157→- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — Created. Barrel re-export facade\n   158→- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` — Created. 19 type verification tests\n   159→- `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — Modified. Added agents subsystem documentation section\n   160→\n   161→## Change Log\n   162→\n   163→- 2026-03-24: Story 13-1 implemented — AgentDriver interface and all supporting types created with full test coverage\n   164→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CTXXCcQ8YHDUe6iJSvW3kn","session_id":"3ce6f3e2-c583-4074-ab3d-b