ication:** `npm run build` succeeds. `npm test` passes all 307 BATS + 3600 vitest tests with zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing TS errors:** `npx tsc --noEmit` reports ~80 type errors across many test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, stack.test.ts, status.test.ts, verify-env.test.ts, etc.). These are all pre-existing and unrelated to this story -- they exist in test files where mocks have incomplete type annotations. The tsup build (which is the actual build tool) succeeds fine.\n- **`RalphDriver.spawn()` uses hardcoded defaults:** The `spawn()` method hardcodes `maxIterations: 50`, `iterationTimeout: 30`, `calls: 100`, `quiet: false` because `SpawnOpts` doesn't carry these ralph-specific options. Story 13-3 (which wires `AgentDriver` into `run.ts`) will need to either extend `SpawnOpts` or pass a configuration object. This is expected per the story's Dev Notes -- `spawn()` currently provides a working implementation, and the real integration happens in 13-3.\n- **`resolveRalphPath()` path calculation changed:** The function now lives two directories deeper (`src/lib/agents/` vs `src/commands/`), so the relative path calculation was adjusted. It traverses up from `src/lib/agents` to the package root. This should work identically in both source and dist layouts.\n- **`parseOutput()` maps `warn` (retry N/M) with `delay: 0`:** The ralph retry message doesn't include a delay value, so `delay` is hardcoded to 0 for retry events parsed from ralph stderr. Stream-json retry events do include the real delay."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab38d34d539b70d8a (use SendMessage with to: 'ab38d34d539b70d8a' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 94623\ntool_uses: 68\nduration_ms: 516612</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3ce6f3e2-c583-4074-ab3d-bf1fc6d87b66","uuid":"bbccb01e-aa52-4095-9f22-847cfdf83759","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:00:55.376Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story a