age`, `parseIterationMessage` and their regexes; now imports from `./agents/ralph.js`\n- `src/commands/run.ts` -- imports `buildSpawnArgs`, `resolveRalphPath` from `../lib/agents/ralph.js`; removed local `resolveRalphPath`; updated re-exports\n- `src/index.ts` -- updated stream-parser import path\n- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` -- updated stream-parser import path\n- `src/__tests__/run-pipeline.test.ts` -- updated stream-parser import path\n- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` -- updated stream-parser import path\n- `src/lib/__tests__/run-helpers.test.ts` -- imports migrated functions from new location\n- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` -- updated mock paths for stream-parser and ralph-prompt\n\n**Verification:** `npm run build` succeeds. `npm test` passes all 307 BATS + 3600 vitest tests with zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing TS errors:** `npx tsc --noEmit` reports ~80 type errors across many test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, stack.test.ts, status.test.ts, verify-env.test.ts, etc.). These are all pre-existing and unrelated to this story -- they exist in test files where mocks have incomplete type annotations. The tsup build (which is the actual build tool) succeeds fine.\n- **`RalphDriver.spawn()` uses hardcoded defaults:** The `spawn()` method hardcodes `maxIterations: 50`, `iterationTimeout: 30`, `calls: 100`, `quiet: false` because `SpawnOpts` doesn't carry these ralph-specific options. Story 13-3 (which wires `AgentDriver` into `run.ts`) will need to either extend `SpawnOpts` or pass a configuration object. This is expected per the story's Dev Notes -- `spawn()` currently provides a working implementation, and the real integration happens in 13-3.\n- **`resolveRalphPath()` path calculation changed:** The function now lives two directories deeper (`src/lib/agents/` vs `src/commands/`), so the relative path calculation was adjusted. It traverses up from `src/lib/agents` to the package root. This should work identically in