{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016wMooQrHn35oVQMBs1Ff3i","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n     2→\n     3→### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — create-story (2026-03-24T11:34:00Z)\n     4→\n     5→- Epic definition had only 1 AC; expanded to 12 ACs by examining codebase\n     6→- Risk: parseStoryKey() returns [Infinity, Infinity] for non-matching keys — edge case needs handling\n     7→- Risk: orphan file deletion (ACs 3-4) is one-way; must delete AFTER successful state write\n     8→- writeStateAtomic() already calls writeSprintStatusYaml() — reconcileState() may cause double YAML generation\n     9→- retry-state.ts has @deprecated comments saying \"will be removed in story 11-3\" for legacy path helpers\n    10→- run.ts still reads ralph/.flagged_stories directly (line 93-101), bypassing sprint-state.json flagged field — must update before file deletion\n    11→\n    12→### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — dev-story (2026-03-24T11:45:00Z)\n    13→\n    14→- Pre-existing ~60 type errors in unrelated test files (not introduced by this story)\n    15→- Readonly mutation workaround: uses JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...)) deep clone + type assertions to mutate SprintState clone\n    16→- YAML always regenerated even in no-op case — cheap but could be optimized to skip if content unchanged\n    17→\n    18→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — create-story (2026-03-24T12:01:00Z)\n    19→\n    20→- Workflow file was `workflow.yaml` not `workflow.md` — skill invocation message referenced `.md` but only `.yaml` existed\n    21→- Subagent was instructed not to modify sprint-status.yaml; main agent had to update manually\n    22→- Risk: runner.ts may push past 300 lines if all private helpers are large (~230 line estimate is rough)\n    23→- Risk: AC11 (integration-required) tests e2e CLI behavior identity, requires real project with test runner configured\n    24→- `coverage.ts` is 633 lines (not 617 as stated in architecture-v3.md — grew since doc was written)\n    25→- This establishes the first domain subdirectory pattern in src/lib/ — stories 12-2 through 12-4 will follow it\n    26→\n    27→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — dev-story (2026-03-24T12:04:00Z)\n    28→\n    29→No issues reported (subagent reported \"None\").\n    30→\n    31→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — code-review (2026-03-24T12:14:00Z)\n    32→\n    33→- HIGH: runner.ts statement coverage at 78.15% (below 80% per-file floor). Fixed — now 95.79% (+11 new tests)\n    34→- MEDIUM (unfixed tech debt): `findCoverageSummary` exported from parser.ts but not from index.ts barrel. Used only by evaluator.ts as sibling import.\n    35→- LOW: `error: required option '--story <key>' not specified` noise during `codeharness coverage` runs from other commands registering at startup\n    36→- No integration test exercises full `runCoverage` pipeline end-to-end (AC11 integration-required)\n    37→- index.ts and types.ts show 0% coverage (pure type exports, expected)\n    38→\n    39→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — verification (2026-03-24T16:33:00Z)\n    40→\n    41→- Docker Desktop daemon not running — blocked black-box verification\n    42→- Attempted Docker start (`open -a Docker`) — did not come up within 100 seconds\n    43→- Workaround: Used unit-testable verification (direct CLI checks) for all cli-verifiable ACs\n    44→- AC11 (integration-required) escalated — genuinely needs Docker for CLI behavior identity testing\n    45→- Proof format issue: initial proof used plain ``` blocks, parser requires ```bash + ```output pairs\n    46→- `codeharness verify` precondition check requires `tests_passed` session flag — had to run `codeharness coverage` first to set it\n    47→- `codeharness coverage --check-only` misparses test counts as \"0 passed, 0 failed\" (output format mismatch)\n    48→\n    49→### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — create-story (2026-03-24T12:43:00Z)\n    50→\n    51→- Epic definition lists otlp.ts as 422 lines but actual measurement shows 453 lines — used actual\n    52→- Epic retrospective (epic-12-retrospective.md) describes a different Epic 12 (verification pipeline integrity) — numbering reused after renumbering\n    53→- Epic ACs extremely terse (only 2 ACs for 4 file splits) — expanded to 13 ACs to match 12-1 granularity\n    54→- Risk: `backends.ts` in observability/ may require new code (ObservabilityBackend interface) not extractable from otlp.ts\n    55→- Risk: `cleanup.ts` in docker/ references functions that may live in `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` instead of docker.ts\n    56→- Risk: `doc-health.ts` at 832 lines — `scanDocHealth` alone is ~196 lines, scanner.ts may exceed 300 lines\n    57→- Test files collectively 3,204 lines — larger than source files (2,253 lines). Test reorg is significant work\n    58→\n    59→### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — dev-story (2026-03-24T13:06:00Z)\n    60→\n    61→- Circular dependency in doc-health: scanner.ts and staleness.ts have mutual dependency. Resolved by extracting shared utilities to types.ts\n    62→- Dynamic import in teardown.ts (`await import('../lib/docker.js')`) missed by initial sed-based import replacement — fixed manually\n    63→- Test files kept as single files moved to __tests__/ dirs rather than split per-module as AC10 suggested (no functional need)\n    64→- beads.ts 300-line limit forced moving types/functions to story-files.ts — story specified them in beads.ts\n    65→- doc-health/types.ts extra file not in story — necessary for circular dependency resolution\n    66→- backends.ts is entirely new code (no backend abstraction in original otlp.ts)\n    67→- cleanup.ts is stubs only — cleanup logic lives in src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts\n    68→\n    69→### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — code-review (2026-03-24T17:19:00Z)\n    70→\n    71→- HIGH: docker/cleanup.ts had 0% coverage — FIXED (added cleanup.test.ts)\n    72→- HIGH: observability/backends.ts had 0% coverage — FIXED (added backends.test.ts)\n    73→- LOW (unfixed): doc-health/index.ts leaks internal utility functions through barrel\n    74→- LOW (unfixed): doc-health/types.ts duplicates SOURCE_EXTENSIONS constant (3 copies)\n    75→- LOW (unfixed): docker/cleanup.ts and observability/backends.ts are placeholder stubs\n    76→- Coverage gap: test files not reorganized per AC10 (monolithic test files moved as-is)\n    77→- staleness.ts at 284 lines, close to 300-line limit\n    78→\n    79→### 12-3-move-status-logic-to-module — dev-story (2026-03-24T13:38:00Z)\n    80→\n    81→No issues reported (subagent reported \"None\").\n    82→\n    83→### 12-3-move-status-logic-to-module — code-review (2026-03-24T13:49:00Z)\n    84→\n    85→- MEDIUM (fixed): Unused import `isSharedStackRunning` in formatters.ts — dead code from extraction\n    86→- MEDIUM (fixed): Unused type import `DockerHealthResult` in formatters.ts\n    87→- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing mock for `modules/verify/index.js` in status.test.ts — tests relied on graceful error handling\n    88→- LOW (unfixed): No dedicated unit tests for formatters.ts or drill-down.ts at module level\n    89→- LOW (unfixed): `printSprintState()` and `handleFullStatusJson()` independently call report generation — potential duplication\n    90→- Coverage gap: `getValidationProgress` integration path only implicitly tested\n    91→\n    92→### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — create-story (2026-03-24T17:55:00Z)\n    93→\n    94→- Ambiguity in epic definition: 2 terse ACs expanded to 10 based on architecture-v3.md and codebase analysis\n    95→- Workaround: Made refactoring 3 files an explicit AC (AC 9) despite epic saying \"not required\" — needed to prove utilities work\n    96→- Risk: `vi.mock()` hoisting interaction with mock factories needs careful handling by dev agent\n    97→- Observation: Existing partial story file was overwritten; original had references to Epic 13 types (AgentDriver) that don't exist yet\n    98→\n    99→### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — dev-story (2026-03-24T18:10:00Z)\n   100→\n   101→- Task 5 deviation: Story specified refactoring docker.test.ts but vi.mock() hoisting prevents using imported factory functions inside vi.mock() callbacks. Replaced with selector.test.ts which was a better fit for buildSprintState/buildStoryEntry usage.\n   102→- Mock factory adoption limitation: createFsMock()/createChildProcessMock() factories are most useful for configuring mock return values (via vi.mocked()), not for vi.mock() declarations. Fundamental Vitest hoisting constraint — story's dev notes example doesn't work as written.\n   103→- No code quality concerns. All files clean, typed, under 300 lines.\n   104→\n   105→### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — code-review (2026-03-24T18:25:00Z)\n   106→\n   107→- MEDIUM (fixed): `createStateMock()` exported phantom functions `readLocalConfig` and `getProjectRoot` that don't exist in codebase. Split into `createStateMock()` and `createSprintStateMock()`.\n   108→- MEDIUM (fixed): Unused `StoryStatus` type import in `state-builders.ts`.\n   109→- MEDIUM (fixed): Inaccurate JSDoc on `createStateMock()` claiming to match two modules while mixing real and nonexistent functions.\n   110→- LOW (unfixed): `selector.test.ts` wraps shared builders in local helpers rather than using `buildSprintState` directly.\n   111→- LOW (unfixed): No `index.ts` barrel file in `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` — consumers must know `helpers.ts` re-export convention.\n   112→- Architecture concern: Mock factories cannot be used with `vi.mock()` directly due to Vitest hoisting — pattern's value limited until more test files refactored.\n   113→\n   114→### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — verification (2026-03-24T18:30:00Z)\n   115→\n   116→- Proof initially failed validation: missing `**Tier:** unit-testable` header required by `validateProofQuality()` to skip black-box enforcement checks\n   117→- Fixed by adding tier header to proof document\n   118→- All 10 ACs passed with direct CLI verification — no Docker needed\n   119→\n   120→### 13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types — create-story (2026-03-24T18:32:00Z)\n   121→\n   122→- Expanded from 2 ACs to 10 ACs based on architecture spec and codebase conventions\n   123→- All ACs tagged cli-verifiable — types-only story with no external system interactions\n   124→- Risk: AC10 (type-level tests) may be shallow — testing type importability is straightforward but verifying discriminated union completeness requires runtime type guards beyond pure type definitions\n   125→\n   126→### 13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types — code-review (2026-03-24T19:40:00Z)\n   127→\n   128→- LOW: `AgentProcess.on('error')` overload not in AC4 spec — kept as useful defensive addition\n   129→- LOW: `createMockProcess()` mock stores handlers but never exposes them for invocation — future driver tests may need richer mock\n   130→- LOW: `Function` type used in mock — may trigger eslint ban-types rule, acceptable in test code\n   131→- No HIGH or MEDIUM issues found — clean types-only story\n   132→- Coverage: 97.09% overall, all 152 files above 80% floor\n   133→\n   134→### 13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types — verification (2026-03-24T19:44:00Z)\n   135→\n   136→- Precondition failed: AGENTS.md staleness for `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures` — checker falls back to root AGENTS.md instead of `src/lib/AGENTS.md`\n   137→- Fixed by creating `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/AGENTS.md` — workaround for fallback logic gap in `checkAgentsMdForModule`\n   138→- All 10 ACs passed unit-testable verification with direct CLI checks\n   139→- Beads sync failed — story file status line not found (likely a parsing issue)\n   140→\n   141→### 13-2-ralph-driver-implementation — create-story (2026-03-24T19:50:00Z)\n   142→\n   143→- Expanded from 2 epic-level ACs to 16